title: BOYS TENNIS STATE FINALS: Indians not surprised by return to finals
text:
Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Jarrett Kelley 
JARRETT KELLEY OF CHESANING unleashes a serve in his No. 4 singles match against Corunna’s Tyler Quirk Tuesday at Corunna. Kelley won 6-2, 7-5. Chesaning defeated Corunna 5-3. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Eddie Murphy, Randy Dorff 
CHESANING’S EDDIE MURPHY, right, makes a return as Owosso’s Randy Dorff, left, looks on during a No.2 doubles match Tuesday at Chesaning. Murphy and teammate Jarrett Kelley defeated Dorff and Blake Vallie 7-5, 6-4. Chesaning defeated Owosso 5-3 to improve its dual-meet record to 5-2. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Jack Muirhead 
CHESANING’S Jack Muirhead leaps to unload an overhead forehand shot against Owosso’s Blake Beaune during a third singles match Tuesday at Chesaning. Muirhead won 6-2, 7-5. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Jared Brown 
CHESANING’S NO. 1 SINGLES PLAYER Jared Brown follows through on a serve Tuesday against Corunna’s Connor Svrcek. Brown won in three sets, 6-7 (tiebreaker 5-7), 6-4, 6-3 in the last match. Posted: Thursday, October 15, 2015 11:00 am BOYS TENNIS STATE FINALS: Indians not surprised by return to finals By JEROME MURPHY Argus-Press Sports Writer The Argus-Press | 0 comments 
CHESANING — The Chesaning boys tennis team is headed back to the Division 4 state finals for the second straight year.
